description: green, wine, red, yellow, blue, orange border, trace of oxidized gold in halo
inscription:
Inscription

Latin inscription in XVI century hand: [St. Elizabeth, Pray for Us]
provenance: Przibram, Vienna (not in Lugt); Colnaghi; Knoedler & Co. [Anderson Galleries, New York, until 1916; sold, for $150, to Jones]; Herschel V. Jones, Minneapolis (1916 - d. May 24, 1928); by descent to Tessie Jones, New York (1928-d.1967); bequeathed to MIA, 1968.
title: St. Elizabeth with a Beggar (Rhenish)
